canonLine Class Reference

A canonLine object represents one canonical command. Each gcode line produces one or more canonical commands. It can either be a motion command (one of LINEAR_TRAVERSE LINEAR_FEED ARC_FEED), or a motionless command (anything else) You cannot create objects of this class - instead, create an object of a class that inherits from this class via canonLineFactory(). Detailed Description

A canonLine object represents one canonical command. Each gcode line produces one or more canonical commands. It can either be a motion command (one of LINEAR_TRAVERSE LINEAR_FEED ARC_FEED), or a motionless command (anything else) You cannot create objects of this class - instead, create an object of a class that inherits from this class via canonLineFactory().
